<h1>Installation</h1>

<p class="lead text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">
    Get SoliLang MVC up and running on your machine in minutes.
</p>

<h2>Prerequisites</h2>

<ul class="space-y-2">
    <li><strong>Rust & Cargo</strong> - Latest stable version (<code>rustc --version</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Node.js</strong> - Version 16 or higher (<code>node --version</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>npm or yarn</strong> - For frontend dependencies</li>
</ul>

<h2>Install SoliLang</h2>

<pre><code class="language-bash"># Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/solilang/solilang.git
cd solilang

# Build the project
cargo build --release

# Install the soli CLI globally
cargo install --path .</code></pre>

<p>Verify the installation:</p>

<pre><code class="language-bash">soli --version</code></pre>

<h2>Create a New Project</h2>

<pre><code class="language-bash"># Clone the MVC example (or create your own)
cd examples/mvc_app

# Install frontend dependencies
npm install

# Build CSS (TailwindCSS)
npm run build:css</code></pre>

<h2>Run the Development Server</h2>

<pre><code class="language-bash"># Start the dev server with hot reload
npm run dev

# Or use the shell script directly
./dev.sh</code></pre>

<p>
    The server will start at <a href="http://localhost:3000" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">http://localhost:3000</a>.
